File location: /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf

You don't "save code" here, but you must ensure the configuration allows the App-VM to connect.

Edit Config: sudo nano /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf

Change bind-address = 127.0.0.1 to bind-address = 0.0.0.0

Restart MySQL: sudo systemctl restart mysql

Database Setup (SQL commands):

SQL

CREATE DATABASE project_db;
CREATE USER 'appuser'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'Akshay@7093';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON project_db.* TO 'appuser'@'%';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

USE project_db;
CREATE TABLE users (id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50), password VARCHAR(50));
INSERT INTO users (username, password) VALUES ('admin', 'Azure123');